e is nationwide.\"}]} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-create-block-content-faqs\"><section class=\"position-relative \" style=\"padding:50px 0;\" id=\"\"><div class=\"container\" style=\"\" id=\"\"><div class=\"row justify-content-center\" style=\"\" id=\"\"><div class=\"\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>Do you accept cases nationwide?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">Yes, my practice is nationwide.</p></div></div></div></div></section></div>\n<!-- /wp:create-block/content-faqs --></div></div></div></section></div>\n<!-- /wp:create-block/content-block -->\n\n<!-- wp:create-block/content-faqs {\"faqs\":[{\"col_class\":\"\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What kind of cases do you consult on?\",\"content\":\"My practice covers various cases involving electrical, electronic, or telecommunications phenomena.\\u003cbr\\u003eI work in both civil and criminal cases for the plaintiff or defense.\\u003cbr\\u003eI have worked with plaintiff and defense lawyers on civil cases in several fields, including wrongful death, personal injury, product liability, medical malpractice, class action, insurance claims, auto accidents, contract disputes, and more.\\u003cbr\\u003eSome criminal cases I’ve worked on have involved securities fraud, homicide, sex trafficking, and home invasion. The criminal cases usually center around cellular, mobile phone, GPS, and other electronic evidence.\"},{\"col_class\":\"\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What kind of cases do you consult on?\",\"content\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"Do you work for the plaintiff, or do you work for the defense?\",\"content\":\"I work for both plaintiff and defense lawyers on civil and criminal cases.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"Are you licensed to practice engineering?\",\"content\":\"Yes, I am a licensed and Board certified engineer. My Board certification comes from the National Academy of Forensic Engineers. Additionally, I am an NCEES “Record Holder, ” meaning I can typically get licensed in any state within 30 days.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What is your availability?\",\"content\":\"I am accepting new cases and am flexible and available on my clients’ schedules. I take pride in meeting all my clients’ deadlines.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What is your billing rate?\",\"content\":\"My rates are very reasonable. I have two set rates for testimony time, such as in deposition or trial. The second, a lower rate, is for all other time (research, report writing, etc.) I collect an initial retainer and invoice against that.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What is your educational background?\",\"content\":\"I’ve been blessed with the opportunity to gain excellent academic credentials.\\u003cbr\\u003eI have a Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering (BSEE) from Lehigh University in Bethlehem, PA. My first Master’s degree is in Telecommunications Engineering, and my second Master’s degree is in Engineering Management- both from the University of Colorado at Boulder. I also completed about 2/3 of an MSEE degree in RF engineering from Drexel University in Philadelphia before moving to Colorado.\\u003cbr\\u003eLastly, I procured the highest credential available in the quality sciences: the Six Sigma Master Black Belt. This required eight graduate courses (24 credit hours) in applied statistics and research at the University of Colorado.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"How many years of experience do you have?\",\"content\":\"I have over 25 years of experience as an engineer and ten years of experience in quality sciences and applied research.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"Do you have trial experience?\",\"content\":\"Yes – I have testified on behalf of the plaintiff and defense at criminal and civil trials.\",\"code_block\":\"\"}]} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-create-block-content-faqs\"><section class=\"position-relative \" style=\"padding:50px 0;\" id=\"\"><div class=\"container\" style=\"\" id=\"\"><div class=\"row justify-content-center\" style=\"\" id=\"\"><div class=\"\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>What kind of cases do you consult on?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">My practice covers various cases involving electrical, electronic, or telecommunications phenomena.<br>I work in both civil and criminal cases for the plaintiff or defense.<br>I have worked with plaintiff and defense lawyers on civil cases in several fields, including wrongful death, personal injury, product liability, medical malpractice, class action, insurance claims, auto accidents, contract disputes, and more.<br>Some criminal cases I’ve worked on have involved securities fraud, homicide, sex trafficking, and home invasion. The criminal cases usually center around cellular, mobile phone, GPS, and other electronic evidence.</p></div></div><div class=\"\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>What kind of cases do you consult on?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\"></p></div></div><div class=\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>Do you work for the plaintiff, or do you work for the defense?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">I work for both plaintiff and defense lawyers on civil and criminal cases.</p></div></div><div class=\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>Are you licensed to practice engineering?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">Yes, I am a licensed and Board certified engineer. My Board certification comes from the National Academy of Forensic Engineers. Additionally, I am an NCEES “Record Holder, ” meaning I can typically get licensed in any state within 30 days.</p></div></div><div class=\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>What is your availability?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">I am accepting new cases and am flexible and available on my clients’ schedules. I take pride in meeting all my clients’ deadlines.</p></div></div><div class=\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>What is your billing rate?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">My rates are very reasonable. I have two set rates for testimony time, such as in deposition or trial. The second, a lower rate, is for all other time (research, report writing, etc.) I collect an initial retainer and invoice against that.</p></div></div><div class=\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>What is your educational background?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">I’ve been blessed with the opportunity to gain excellent academic credentials.<br>I have a Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering (BSEE) from Lehigh University in Bethlehem, PA. My first Master’s degree is in Telecommunications Engineering, and my second Master’s degree is in Engineering Management- both from the University of Colorado at Boulder. I also completed about 2/3 of an MSEE degree in RF engineering from Drexel University in Philadelphia before moving to Colorado.<br>Lastly, I procured the highest credential available in the quality sciences: the Six Sigma Master Black Belt. This required eight graduate courses (24 credit hours) in applied statistics and research at the University of Colorado.</p></div></div><div class=\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>How many years of experience do you have?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">I have over 25 years of experience as an engineer and ten years of experience in quality sciences and applied research.</p></div></div><div class=\"col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch\" style=\"\"><div class=\"undefined\" style=\"undefined\"><h3>Do you have trial experience?</h3><p style=\"margin-bottom:0px\">Yes – I have testified on behalf of the plaintiff and defense at criminal and civil trials.</p></div></div></div></div></section></div>\n<!-- /wp:create-block/content-faqs -->\n\n<!-- wp:create-block/content-block {\"section_style\":\"padding:0px;background:#F7F7F7;\",\"col_class\":\"col-12 text-center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-create-block-content-block\"><section class=\"position-relative \" style=\"padding:50px 0;padding:0px;background:#F7F7F7;\" id=\"\"><div class=\"container\" style=\"\" id=\"\"><div class=\"row justify-content-center\" style=\"\" id=\"\"><div class=\"col-12 text-center\" style=\"\" id=\"\" data-aos=\"fade-up\" data-aos-delay=\"\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":33,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://discovery-engineering.local/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Discovery-Engineering-Professional-Engineers.png\" alt=\"Discovery-Engineering-Professional-Engineers\" class=\"wp-image-33\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div></div></div></section></div>\n<!-- /wp:create-block/content-block -->','Electrical Engineer Expert Witness - Mark McFarland, P.E.','','inherit','closed','closed','','2-revision-v1','','','2024-04-18 01:08:57','2024-04-18 01:08:57','',2,'http://discovery-engineering.local/?p=183',0,'revision','',0),(184,1,'2024-04-18 01:09:21','2024-04-18 01:09:21','<!-- wp:create-block/two-columns {\"col_code\":\"\\u003cifram